# Scraper Pipeline Conventions

## Runtime Path
Canonical flow: `tasks.py` → `discovery.py` / `service.py` → `scraper_pool.py` → `extractors.py`.
There is no `engine.py` — it was removed. Do not create or reference it.

## Fetch Layer (scraper_pool.py)
Priority order: Decodo API → httpx → Playwright.
If `requires_js=True` on marketplace, Playwright moves above httpx.
`ScraperPool` is the ONLY fetch+extract facade. All scraping goes through it.
Price overflow guard: `MAX_VALID_PRICE = 9_999_999_999.99`. Prices above this or ≤ 0 are discarded (set to None).

## Extraction Layer (extractors.py)
Priority: JSON-LD → meta tags → custom selectors → auto-detect heuristics → merge.
No marketplace-specific hardcoding — extraction is universal.
`extract_product_links` has strict URL filtering: excludes /list/, /category/, /catalog/, /search.
`parse_price_text` supports locale formats with `,` and `.` separators.

## Persistence (service.py)
`GlobalScrapeService.scrape_product` is SYNCHRONOUS (sync Session for Celery workers).
Only `ScraperPool.scrape_product` runs async via `_run_coro_in_worker()`.

On `result.success`:
- Clear `listing.last_error` and `listing.consecutive_errors` immediately.
- Write `fact_price` only when: product_name or title present, price > 0, currency non-empty.
- Update `dim_product.name` from title if product_name is empty.

On `not result.success`:
- Increment `consecutive_errors`, set `last_error`.

`_today_date_id`: SELECT → INSERT ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING → flush → SELECT (deadlock-safe).
`last_in_stock`: chain `result.in_stock` → `data.in_stock` → `False` (never NULL).

## Logging Pattern
- `EXTRACTED →` — raw extractor fields.
- `FINAL PERSIST` — values before commit.
- `SCRAPE COMPLETE listing_id=… status=… price=…` — after successful commit.
- `pool_scrape done` — task completion.

## scrape_logs Status Values
`success`, `error`, `timeout`, `blocked`, `captcha`, `not_found`, `price_not_found`, `parse_error`, `missing_critical_data`, `technical_error`.
Status column is VARCHAR(50) with CHECK constraint (migrations 005–006); canonical tuple: `errors.SCRAPE_LOG_STATUSES`.

## Discovery (discovery.py)
- Level 1: find category URLs from homepage/sitemap.
- Level 2: extract product URLs from each category.
- Each product URL creates `DimProduct` (placeholder) + `FactListing` (url_hash dedupe).
- Batch commit every 50 records with rollback recovery.
- Updates `marketplace.last_discovery_*` and `products_in_pool`.

## Celery Tasks
- Pool scrape tasks use `sync_session_factory` — no async session.
- Discovery tasks use local async engine + `_run_async`.
- `scrape_pool_product`: soft_time_limit=120, time_limit=150.
- Unhandled exceptions → `_persist_technical_error_log` with status `technical_error`.
- Beat schedule is currently empty (`{}`). Do not enable without explicit permission.

## Contracts
- `PoolScrapeResult`: success, url, data, scraper_layer, duration_ms, error, is_partial, is_empty, fields_extracted, fields_missing.
- `DiscoveryResult`: marketplace_id, status, timing, counters, errors, discovery_method.
- `ExtractedProduct`: title, price, currency (NO `in_stock` field — use safe getattr).
